    • setLocAllowedFreshTime

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setLocAllowedFreshTime(int timeout)
      In milli seconds, for GPS location, if the location value time stamp is within this time frame, send that value as location signals to GAH backend. If the location timestamp is older than this value, request for a new set of location co-ordinates.

      Default is 15mins.

      Parameters:
      timeout - value in ms until location cached value to be considered
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setLocBackgroundCollectionTime

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setLocBackgroundCollectionTime(int timeout)
      In milli seconds, the time allowed to get location at background. Once requested, Location signal collection and caching the values will continue in background thread until this timeout. Higher the timeout value might lead to higher battery consumption.

      Default value is 30sec

      Parameters:
      timeout - Background collection timeout value in ms
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setLocFetchTime

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setLocFetchTime(int timeout)
      In milli seconds, The time allowed to get the location since the request for location co-ordinates is made. If the OS does not return the location within this timeout, location signals will be considered as status not found. Higher value will make better possibility of location signal collection at the cost of increased latency in signal collection.

      Default value is 50ms

      Parameters:
      timeout - Location fetch timeout value in ms
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setSignalPrefetchTime

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setSignalPrefetchTime(int prefetchTimeout)
      In seconds, maximum time to prefetch signals and cache the values. GAHPrefetchStatusCallback callback will be given to the application (if requested by application using requestPrefetchStatus()) at the end of this timeout, with success/failure status of prefetch. This timeout will override all previous configuration timeout such as ProfileRequestTimeout in GTMTMXConfig.

      Default value is 5seconds

      Parameters:
      prefetchTimeout - Prefetch timeout in seconds
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.1.0

    • setSignalCacheTime

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setSignalCacheTime(int cacheTimeout)
      In seconds, maximum time for which prefetched signals will be cached. Signal values older than this timeout will not be considered during risk calculation, GAH SDK will collect a fresh value during very next call to requestVisitId() after Signal cache timeout. This timeout will override all previous configuration for the cache time out such as SessionIDTimeout in GTMTMXConfig.

      Default value is 300seconds.

      Parameters:
      cacheTimeout - Cache timeout in seconds
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.1.0

    • setFetchTimeout

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setFetchTimeout(int timeout)
      In milli seconds, The time allowed to get the signals. If the system does not return the signals within this timeout, signals will be considered as status TIMEOUT. The timeout value given here will be common for all Signal Providers except Location.

      Default value is 2000 ms

      Parameters:
      timeout - fetch timeout value in ms
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.2.0

    • setLocationAccuracy

      public GAHGemaltoSignalConfig.Builder setLocationAccuracy(int accuracy)
      In meters, Horizontal accuracy, radial with which location co-ordinates to be collected. These location co-ordinates will be used to get Reverse geo data for Country code and Country name signals. Default value is 100 meters
      Parameters:
      accuracy - fetch timeout value in ms
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.2.0
